Requires INTERCEPTOR feature (not yet implemented)

This test attempts "pass-through" tap behavior:
  ~tap(source -> dest)
  | result r |> log(...)
      | done |> result { result: r }  ← Pass through original result

Taps are OBSERVE-ONLY. To transform/pass-through payloads, we need
the INTERCEPTOR feature designed in 365_INTERCEPTORS/SPEC.md:
  ~intercept(* -> dest)
  | payload p |> payload { ...transformed... }

Once interceptors are implemented, this test should be updated to use
~intercept() instead of ~tap() for the pass-through behavior.
